msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (_pācittiya_)"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:0.4"
msgid "Acelakavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 42"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:0.5"
msgid "42. Uyyojanasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on sending away"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.93, pts-cs-bu-pc42.1, pts-vp-en.2.351, ms2V_880 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upanando sakyaputto bhātuno saddhivihārikaṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "At that time Venerable Upananda the Sakyan said to his brother’s student,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:1.3"
msgid "“ehāvuso, gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pavisissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Come, let’s go to the village for alms.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:1.4"
msgid "Tassa adāpetvā uyyojesi—"
msgstr "Then, without getting him any food, he sent him away, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:1.5"
msgid "“gacchāvuso, na me tayā saddhiṃ kathā vā nisajjā vā phāsu hoti, ekakassa me kathā vā nisajjā vā phāsu hotī”ti."
msgstr "“Go away, I’m not comfortable talking or sitting with you, but only if I talk and sit by myself.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:1.6"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu upakaṭṭhe kāle nāsakkhi piṇḍāya carituṃ, paṭikkamanepi bhattavissaggaṃ na sambhāvesi, chinnabhatto ahosi."
msgstr "But since the right time for eating was coming to an end, that student was not able to walk for alms. And while he was going back, there was nobody offering food, and so he missed his meal."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms2V_881 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:1.7"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu ārāmaṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "He then went to the monastery and told the monks."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:1.8"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:1.9"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized Upananda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:1.10"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto bhikkhuṃ—‘ehāvuso, gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pavisissāmā’ti tassa adāpetvā uyyojessatī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can Venerable Upananda say to another monk, ‘Come, let’s go to the village for alms,’ and then send him away without getting him any food?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:1.11"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, bhikkhuṃ—‘ehāvuso, gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pavisissāmā’ti tassa adāpetvā uyyojesī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Upananda, that you did this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:1.12"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:1.13"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:1.14"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, bhikkhuṃ—“ehāvuso, gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pavisissāmā”ti tassa adāpetvā uyyojessasi."
msgstr "Foolish man, how can you say to another monk, ‘Come, let’s go to the village for alms,’ and then send him away without getting him any food?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:1.15"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:1.16"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:1.16a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule">
#. VAR: bhikkhuṃ—‘ehāvuso → bhikkhuṃ evaṃ vadeyya ehāvuso (syā1-3)
#. REF: sc3, ms2V_882
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:1.17"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ—‘ehāvuso, gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya pavisissāmā’ti tassa dāpetvā vā adāpetvā vā uyyojeyya—"
msgstr "‘If a monk says to another monk, “Come, let’s go to the village/town for alms,” and then, whether he has had food given to him or not, sends him away, saying,"

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.352 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:1.18"
msgid "‘gacchāvuso, na me tayā saddhiṃ kathā vā nisajjā vā phāsu hoti, ekakassa me kathā vā nisajjā vā phāsu hotī’ti, etadeva paccayaṃ karitvā anaññaṃ, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "“Go away, I’m not comfortable talking or sitting with you, but only if I talk and sit by myself,” and he does so only for this reason and no other, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc4, pts-cs-bu-pc42.2.1, ms2V_883
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.1.2"
msgid "yo, yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc5, ms2V_884
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.1.6"
msgid "Bhikkhunti"
msgstr "Another monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.1.7"
msgid "aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ."
msgstr "a different monk."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc6, ms2V_885
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.1.8"
msgid "Ehāvuso, gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vāti"
msgstr "Come […] to the village/town:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.1.9"
msgid "gāmopi nigamopi nagarampi, gāmo ceva nigamo ca."
msgstr "a village, also a town, also a city; both a village and a town."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc7, ms2V_886
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.1.10"
msgid "Tassa dāpetvāti"
msgstr "He has had food given to him:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.1.11"
msgid "yāguṃ vā bhattaṃ vā khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā dāpetvā."
msgstr "he has had rice-porridge, a meal, non-staples, or staples given to him."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc8, ms2V_887
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.1.12"
msgid "Adāpetvāti"
msgstr "Not:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.1.13"
msgid "na kiñci dāpetvā."
msgstr "he has not had anything given to him."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc9, ms2V_888
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.1.14"
msgid "Uyyojeyyāti"
msgstr "Sends away:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.1.15"
msgid "mātugāmena saddhiṃ hasitukāmo kīḷitukāmo raho nisīditukāmo anācāraṃ ācaritukāmo evaṃ vadeti—"
msgstr "if, wanting to laugh with a woman, wanting to amuse himself with her, wanting to sit down in private with her, wanting to misconduct himself with her, he says,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.1.16"
msgid "“gacchāvuso, na me tayā saddhiṃ kathā vā nisajjā vā phāsu hoti, ekakassa me kathā vā nisajjā vā phāsu hotī”ti uyyojeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "“Go away, I’m not comfortable talking or sitting with you, but only if I talk and sit by myself,” and he sends him away, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.1.17"
msgid "Dassanūpacāraṃ vā savanūpacāraṃ vā vijahantassa āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If the other monk is in the process of going beyond eyesight or earshot, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.1.18"
msgid "Vijahite, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "When the other monk has gone beyond, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc10, ms2V_889
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.1.19"
msgid "Etadeva paccayaṃ karitvā anaññanti"
msgstr "He does so only for this reason and no other:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.1.20"
msgid "na añño koci paccayo hoti uyyojetuṃ."
msgstr "there is no other reason for sending him away."

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc11, pts-cs-bu-pc42.2.2, ms2V_890 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.2.1"
msgid "Upasampanne upasampannasaññī uyyojeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If the other monk is fully ordained, and he perceives him as fully ordained, and he sends him away, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.2.2"
msgid "Upasampanne vematiko uyyojeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If the other monk is fully ordained, but he is unsure if he is, and he sends him away, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.2.3"
msgid "Upasampanne anupasampannasaññī uyyojeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If the other monk is fully ordained, but he does not perceive him as fully ordained, and he sends him away, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12, pts-vp-pli4.94, ms2V_891 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.2.4"
msgid "Kalisāsanaṃ āropeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he puts him down in front of others, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.2.5"
msgid "Anupasampannaṃ uyyojeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he sends away one who is not fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.353 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.2.6"
msgid "Kalisāsanaṃ āropeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he puts him down in front of others, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.2.7"
msgid "Anupasampanne upasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If the other monk is not  fully ordained, but he perceives him as fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.2.8"
msgid "Anupasampanne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If the other monk is not fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.2.9"
msgid "Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If the other monk is not fully ordained, and he perceives him as not fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc13, pts-cs-bu-pc42.2.3, ms2V_892 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.3.2"
msgid "“ubho ekato na yāpessāmā”ti uyyojeti,"
msgstr "if he sends him away, thinking, “Together we won’t get enough;”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.3.3"
msgid "“mahagghaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ passitvā lobhadhammaṃ uppādessatī”ti uyyojeti,"
msgstr "if he sends him away, thinking, “If he sees these valuable things, he’ll become greedy;”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.3.4"
msgid "“mātugāmaṃ passitvā anabhiratiṃ uppādessatī”ti uyyojeti,"
msgstr "if he sends him away, thinking, “If he sees this woman, he’ll become discontent with the monastic life;”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.3.5"
msgid "“gilānassa vā ohiyyakassa vā vihārapālassa vā yāguṃ vā bhattaṃ vā khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā nīharā”ti uyyojeti,"
msgstr "if he sends him away, saying, “Take the rice-porridge/the meal/the non-staples/the staples to the one who is sick/to the one who is left behind/to the one who is guarding the dwelling;”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.3.6"
msgid "na anācāraṃ ācaritukāmo,"
msgstr "if he does not want to misconduct himself;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.3.7"
msgid "sati karaṇīye uyyojeti,"
msgstr "if he sends him away when there is a reason;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.3.8"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.3.9"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc14, ms2V_893 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc42:2.3.10"
msgid "Uyyojanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ."
msgstr "The second rule, the training rule on sending away, is finished."
